	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002327_0001"/><!--pb/@n='74r'-->
<lb/><p rend="center">Burnbank Road</p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><placeName>Hamilton</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">3 June 1865</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>In reference to 
<lb/>the plan of giving 
<lb/>some copies to 
<lb/>Friends how 
<lb/>many do you 
<lb/>propose to be 
<lb/>so disposed of? 
<lb/>And as I have a 
<lb/>little time now 
<lb/>that my mother 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002327_0002"/><!--pb/@n='74v'-->
<lb/>lingers, would it be 
<lb/>worth while to 
<lb/>write an autographic 
<lb/>with comp<hi rend="sup">ts</hi><!-- Expand this abbreviation? --> or 
<lb/>other words to be 
<lb/>pasted inside - 
<lb/>some people like 
<lb/>the autograph - 
<lb/>It might please 
<lb/>them &amp; not hurt 
<lb/>me.</p>
<lb/><p>I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002327_0003"/><!--pb/@n='75r'-->
<lb/><p>You might be able 
<lb/>to suggest some 
<lb/>men who would 
<lb/>take it kind of us 
<lb/>and make the 
<lb/>work known. 
<lb/>I know <persName>Spurgeon</persName><reg>,</reg>
<lb/><persName>Newman</persName><reg>,</reg><persName>Hall</persName><reg>,</reg>
<lb/><persName>Binney</persName> - <persName>Whewell</persName><reg>,</reg>
<lb/><persName>Sedgwick</persName> &amp;c.</p>
			
</div>
